text: Minishty () is a rural locality (a selo) in Mayadykovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 561 as of 2010. There are 12 streets. == Geography == It is located 34 km from Dyurtyuli. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Minishty
